cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI 

This paper is about the Oriental Language Recognition (OLR) challenge, which involves speech recognition and language identification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of i-vector models and neural networks, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The data used in the challenge is provided by SpeechOcean and the NSFC M2ASR project, which are related to speech and audio processing, indicating that cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper reports baseline results evaluated with various metrics, which suggests that cs.LG (Learning) is a possible category as well.
